<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-19031] When camel saga do compensated, the saga route don&apos;t stop it still run the next task.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-19031</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The problem is : I find that when actionA is timeout and it executed compensated, In theory the saga route should be stopped, not continue to call the next actionB.&#160; In my test show that when &lt;font color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;&gt;the first task can&apos;t complete before its timeout, it will run compensation but the saga route don&apos;t stop, it still run second task and third task&lt;/font&gt;. In my opinion, I think when the first task can&apos;t complete and run compensation, the second and third task shouldn&apos;t run. &#160;[Test Code|&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/chen19980/SAGA_timeout_test&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/chen19980/SAGA_timeout_test&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/p&gt;</description>
