                            <comment id="17687777" author="zhfeng" created="Mon, 13 Feb 2023 07:44:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that InMemorySagaCoordinator::beginStep does not check the current status. So even the status is not &lt;b&gt;RUNNING&lt;/b&gt;, it still add the step. Then a potential fix could be to add a status checking. I create a patch as an attachement, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chen19980&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chen19980&quot;&gt;chen19980&lt;/a&gt; can you verify it? &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13055372/13055372_InMemorySagaCoordinator.patch&quot; title=&quot;InMemorySagaCoordinator.patch attached to CAMEL-19031&quot;&gt;InMemorySagaCoordinator.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
